==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muskmelon
<hw>Musk"mel`on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Musk</ets> +
<ets>melon</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The fruit of a
cucurbitaceous plant (<spn>Cucumis Melo</spn>) of the gourd family,
having a peculiar aromatic flavor, and cultivated in many varieties, the
principal sorts being the cantaloupe, of oval form and yellowish flesh,
and the smaller nutmeg melon with greenish flesh. See <xex>Illust.</xex>
of <er>Melon</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muskogees</ent>⟦br⟧
